<title type="html"><![CDATA[Can square wave echoes cancel the other wave?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5385&amp;p=48750#p48750"><![CDATA[
Yeah but if they almost cancel, a very annoying sound is heard. One solution is to use a different duty cycle for the echo, or do what memblers says if your sound engine is complex enough to support that. (when 50% square echoes a 75% or 87.5% rectangle wave it sounds cool).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Jul 10, 2009 3:47 am</p><hr />
