<author><name><![CDATA[Jarhmander]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-07-09T19:30:40-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-07-09T19:30:40-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5385&amp;p=48740#p48740</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5385&amp;p=48740#p48740"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Can square wave echoes cancel the other wave?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5385&amp;p=48740#p48740"><![CDATA[
If you do some writes in $4003/$4007 to both square waves to the start of the note, they will be always sync'd, since writing to these registers reset the phase, so no wave cancelling is possible.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=336">Jarhmander</a> — Thu Jul 09, 2009 7:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
